-- H&M sales up in January
-- 
-- Fri Feb 15, 2008 2:08am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/15/us-hm-sales-idUSSAB01891720080215

 

 STOCKHOLM  (Reuters) - Swedish fashion giant Hennes & Mauritz ( HMb.ST ) reported on Friday a 3 percent rise in sales in stores open more than a year in January, lagging market expectations. 

 The average in a poll of 10 analysts by Reuters was for a 5.1 percent rise in like-for-like sales. Sweden's biggest company by market capitalization, said total turnover for the month was up 17 percent. It had already announced a rise in total sales up to January 29 of 16 percent, in parallel with its fourth-quarter results.